<br>
But back to the original question ... a lot of the &quot;immersiveness&quot; depends on the player. There really is a lot going on; especially prime time. But if you're still camping loot/XP in the same ol' spots as your original server, you're going to miss it.<br>
<br>
Although even that is not always true. A few times when a guild has killed an uber mob, the GMs jump in and start an event based off of it. For example, one guild killed the AoW. Shortly after, a GM controlled version of Rallos Zek appeared and rallied the giants for war. Giants were created and marched to GD for eventual battle at Thurg (much like is done for the 10th ring quest) but with GMs involved as NPCs on both sides. The battle lasted nearly 3 hours if I remember right.<br>
<br>
Anyway ... I'm enjoying SH a lot.<br>
<br>
But the warning about low level characters someone made is true. For whatever reason, about 80-90% of the folks there are over level 50. It's nearly impossible to get a group at lower levels. 'Course if you are a soloing class, you basically get complete reign over all the prime hunting sites <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
